CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 21, 1959, pg. 9, reads: "Accent On Paris - Five of the beautiful young models who took part in D.I. fashion show-cabaret party Sunday night at the New Arena Supper Club show the extreme chic of their outfits...Center: Lovely Hilda Logan wears her own creations. This is a shirred front cocktail dress in warm yellow-orange satin, which fits her closely, but beautifully.... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Hilda Logan wearing yellow-orange satin dress gathered through middle, jeweled brooch at neckline, and tiara, standing in front of wooden bench with tufted cushion, in interior of the New Arena Supper Club for D.I. "March" benefit for the National Foundation
